So one thing how docker does it that it adds a step `LABEL <key>=<value>` as last child step to parsed nodes when `--label` is provided however `podman/buildah` does not functions in the same manner as we are not treating labeling as a step when specified from command line instead we are just adding labels explicitly during `commit(`  and that does not adds this step to  history. In case of `podman/buildah`  a simpler fix would be

```diff
--- a/imagebuildah/stage_executor.go
+++ b/imagebuildah/stage_executor.go
@@ -894,7 +896,25 @@ func (s *StageExecutor) Execute(ctx context.Context, base string) (imgID string,
                                }
                                break
                        }
-               }
+               } else {
+                       // If layers or cache is being used
+                       // and this is a last step commit if
+                       // labels or annotations has been changed
+                       // by the user explicitly using cmd line.
+                       if len(s.executor.labels) > 0 || len(s.executor.annotations) > 0 {
+                               if lastStage || imageIsUsedLater {
+                                       logCommit(s.output, i)
+                                       imgID, ref, err = s.commit(ctx, s.getCreatedBy(node, ""), false, s.output)
+                                       if err != nil {
+                                               return "", nil, errors.Wrapf(err, "error committing container for step %+v", *step)
+                                       }
+                                       logImageID(imgID)
+                               } else {
+                                       imgID = ""
+                               }
+                               break
+                       }
+               }
```

however this not going to part of the history diff therefore we are not going to leverage `cache` as good as docker is doing whenever `--label` is used, a better fix would be we follow same path as docker. But i want to still confirm this from @containers/buildah-maintainers  if this is intentional or unknown behavior for the case of `--labels` before creating any PR.
